Kenya Kwanza on Saturday stormed Nyahururu in Laikipia County in a hunt for votes. The team was led by the Alliance's presidential candidate William Ruto. They made a stop at Nyandarua County where they held an Economic Forum in Ol Jororok. The Alliance committed to turning agriculture — the region’s main source of livelihood — into a profitable venture. He was accompanied by his running mate Rigathi Gachagus, Speaker of the National Assembly Justin Muturi and Moses Kuria (CCK). MPs Faith Gitau (Nyandarua), Michael Muchira (Oljoroorok), Ndindi Nyoro(Kiharu), Wanjiku Muhia (EALA) and other allied leaders were also present.